# Wireless regulatory domain
# /etc/conf.d/wireless-regdom
#
# Sets the wireless regulatory domain for WiFi channel and power limits.
# Different countries have different allowed frequencies and power levels.
#
# IMPORTANT: The installer will prompt you to set your country code.
# If you're not in the US, change this value to your country code.
#
# Using the wrong regdom may:
#   - Prevent access to certain WiFi channels
#   - Limit transmit power (reduced range)
#   - Violate local radio regulations
#
# List available regdoms: iw reg get
# Check current regdom:   iw reg get | head -1
#
# Common codes: US, GB, DE, FR, JP, AU, CA, CN, KR, TW, IN, BR, MX
#
# Validated: File location and format correct per Arch Wiki.
# See: https://wiki.archlinux.org/title/Network_configuration/Wireless#Respecting_the_regulatory_domain

WIRELESS_REGDOM="US"
